scene.message:
Yukino: What?! This room{nl}
feels different from the{nl}
others. Someone's dream too?{waitkey}{clearbox}Hm? Someone's in the back!{waitkey}{ret}

???: Indeed...{nl}
shall we show them{nl}
some hospitality?{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: What? She's wearing{nl}
our school's uniform.{nl}
Is this her dream?{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: Whoa-ho!{nl}
She's a pretty cute girl!{nl}
Huh huh?!{waitkey}{clearbox}Hey! Hey!!{nl}
She's wearing our{nl}
school's uniform!!{waitkey}{clearbox}How did I, of all people,{nl}
fail to notice her?!{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Hey, you,{nl}
which class are you from?{nl}
Are you trapped in{waitkey}here too?{waitkey}{ret}

???: Heehee.{nl}
It's you who should say{nl}
why you're here.{waitkey}{clearbox}This is a dream of mine,{nl}
by mine,{nl}
for mine alone.{waitkey}{clearbox}Yes - this is the dream of{nl}
"Kumi Hirose," entrusted by{nl}
the Snow Queen to guard this{waitkey}"Tower of Hypnos."{waitkey}{clearbox}Barging into another's dream{nl}
with muddy feet - how{nl}
rude you all are.{waitkey}Right, Lord Hypnos?{waitkey}{ret}

Hypnos: Indeed, Kumi.{nl}
Another's dream is one thing,{nl}
but to enter Kumi's dream -{waitkey}they don't know their place.{waitkey}{clearbox}What say you, Kumi?{nl}
If it's all right with you,{nl}
I could punish{waitkey}them a little.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: The tower's master?{nl}
So you're the ones putting{nl}
the school's people to sleep{waitkey}{clearbox}and trapping them in the{nl}
"Anti-Dream World."{waitkey}{clearbox}Why not kill them outright{nl}
than this roundabout way?{waitkey}{clearbox}Sealing human souls in the{nl}
"Anti-Dream World" -{nl}
what are you plotting?!{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: The tower's master?{nl}
So you're the ones putting{nl}
the school's people to sleep{waitkey}and sealing them in the{nl}
"Anti-Dream World."{waitkey}{clearbox}Surely you could slaughter{nl}
them all with ease.{waitkey}{clearbox}For what purpose do you seal{nl}
people's souls in the{nl}
"Anti-Dream World"?!{waitkey}{ret}

Kumi: ...heh... heehee...{nl}
I wondered what you'd ask,{nl}
and it's that...{waitkey}{clearbox}I suppose it can't be helped.{nl}
You too are unfortunate{nl}
souls forced to live in{waitkey}the real world.{waitkey}{clearbox}Isn't it obvious? Because{nl}
people are happiest living{nl}
within a dream.{waitkey}{clearbox}In the real world, people{nl}
can never find happiness...{waitkey}{clearbox}I'm merely teaching{nl}
that to everyone.{nl}
Right, Lord Hypnos?{waitkey}{ret}

Hypnos: Indeed, Kumi.{nl}
Kumi's not at fault at all.{nl}
The ones to blame are... them.{waitkey}{clearbox}But it can't be helped that{nl}
they can't understand{nl}
Kumi.{waitkey}{clearbox}They know nothing of how{nl}
cruelly Kumi was treated{nl}
in the real world...{waitkey}{clearbox}nor with what feelings she{nl}
came to this dream world...{nl}
nothing at all.{waitkey}{clearbox}Come, let us show them{nl}
what Kumi went through{nl}
in the real world.{waitkey}{clearbox}And let us teach them{nl}
the wonder of the{nl}
dream world!!{waitkey}{ret}
